If they do keep the Munster manse, it will need not just a grand room, but a &lt;i&gt;great&lt;/i&gt; room.  And more closets!  Lots of closets!  And a marble kitchen, and lots of diamond-encrusted Lucite furniture.  And marble walls!  Which can then be sprayed with an ocean of faux-marble paint.  Solid gold fixtures!  Flatscreens in every bathroom!  And everything has to be child-proofed!  Think of the children!!!  Geez, youâ€<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2122.png" alt="™" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />d think Iâ€<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/2122.png" alt="™" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />d been doing this for years.  This is going to be the greatest entablature-and-frieze-coated Tuscan palace on the block.  I mean, if the bungalow next door could be transformed into a mansarded Regency in the 50s (the 1950s), why not?
